.tgz file creation in Bash 
cd to the location of the directory you want to .tgz

tar -czvf Splunk_TA_TrendMicro.tgz Splunk_TA_TrendMicro
tar -czvf 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_aws_customTA.tgz 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_aws_customTA


Un Tar a .tgz file in Linux bash into it's current directory 
tar -xzvf 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_aws_customTA.tgz
tar -xzvf 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_aws_customTA.tgz -C /path/to/destination/


To verify the contents of the .tgz file:

tar -tzf 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_AWS_100.tgz


Move .tgz file to deploy directory

mv 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_AWS_100.tgz /opt/splunk/apps/ready_to_deploy/


Move both .tgz file to deploy directory

mv 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_AWS_100.tgz 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100.tgz /opt/splunk/apps/ready_to_deploy/


grep | How do i grep to see if i have the app tenable

cd $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps
ls -larth | grep -i tenable

ls -larth $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps | grep -i tenable
ls -larth /opt/splunk/etc/apps/ | grep -i tenable



How to create Directorys & Files in Linux Bash 

# Navigate to the apps directory
cd /opt/splunk/etc/apps

# Create the main directory structure
mkdir -p 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default
mkdir -p 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/metadata

# Create the empty configuration files in default/
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default/app.conf
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default/props.conf
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default/transforms.conf
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default/eventtypes.conf
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/default/tags.conf

# Create the metadata file
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/metadata/default.meta

# Create the app manifest file
touch 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/app.manifest

# Verify the structure was created
tree 02-ns2-us-Splunk_TA_Azure_100/    
